comments: Holmes (SAC) gathers the pass and takes fewer than three steps prior to the start of his dribble.
Holiday (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Barnes (SAC).  The contact during the pick is marginal.
Holiday (MIL) makes contact with Haliburton's (SAC) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Barnes (SAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Connaughton (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position during Barnes' (SAC) driving shot attempt.
Davis (SAC) makes incidental contact to Holiday's (MIL) body following the play at the basket.
Portis (MIL) gives Haliburton (SAC) room to land following the jump shot attempt. The foot to foot contact that occurs is marginal. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Davis (SAC) is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to MIL.
Middleton (MIL) makes contact with Barnes (SAC) during the inbound that affects his ability to defend the pass.
Davis (SAC) attempts to commit a take foul on Holiday (MIL) but makes marginal contact.
Davis (SAC) commits a take foul on DiVincenzo (MIL).
Barnes (SAC) commits a take foul on Middleton (MIL).
Haliburton (SAC) commits a take foul on DiVincenzo (MIL).
Haliburton (SAC) commits a take foul on Middleton (MIL).
Middleton (MIL) makes marginal contact with Holmes (SAC) off ball that does not affect his ability to get to the pass.
